## 1. Missing global error handling
No `try/catch` or Express error-handling middleware. An unhandled throw will crash the process or leak stack traces.

```js
// 404 handler
app.use((req, res) => res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }));

// Central error handler (must have 4 args)
app.use((err, req, res, _next) => {
  console.error(err);
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});

// Process-level safety nets
process.on('unhandledRejection', (r) => console.error('unhandledRejection', r));
process.on('uncaughtException', (e) => { console.error(e); process.exit(1); });
```

## 2. `app.listen` has no error handler
