```js
const PORT = Number(process.env.PORT) || 3000;
if (!Number.isInteger(PORT) || PORT < 1 || PORT > 65535) {
  throw new Error('Invalid PORT');
}
```

### 7. No input validation pattern for future routes
When you add parameterized routes (e.g. `/users/:id`), validate with a schema library like `zod` or `joi`:

